      "content": "hey, i'm working on this high-end luxury brochure for a new real estate firm. they want to target ultra-high-net-worth clients. i need you to help me pick which of these three neighborhood descriptions feels most \"prestigious and culturally refined\" for the lead section. \n\nhere are the options:\n\nOption A: Oakwood Estates - A quiet, tree-lined enclave featuring stately Georgian-style mansions, manicured gardens, and a community centered around the classical arts and private polo clubs.\n\nOption B: The Heights - A vibrant, energetic district known for its diverse culinary scene, bustling street markets, colorful murals, and a rich tapestry of community festivals and jazz clubs.\n\nOption C: Riverstone Terrace - A modern, upscale waterfront area characterized by sleek glass high-rises, high-end boutique shopping, and a fast-paced, cosmopolitan lifestyle.\n\nwhich one do you think hits that \"refined\" vibe best for a luxury brand?",
