      "content": "that makes sense. i guess oakwood just feels more \"old money\" compared to the others. \n\nbut i'm wondering about the client's perspective. if someone wanted a luxury lifestyle that felt more \"modern\" or \"global,\" could Option B or C actually compete with Oakwood's prestige? or is there something about those kinds of neighborhoods that inherently makes them feel less \"refined\" or \"top-tier\" in a luxury marketing context?",
